<P>
   RAC-SARATOGA (Undated) _ The highlight of the New York racing
season _ six weeks in Saratoga _ begins on Wednesday. The opening
stakes race is the $100,000 Grade II Schuylerville for 2-year-old
fillies. By Joseph Durso.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-SWIM-HEYNS (Undated) _ Day after day, for more than two
months in early 1998, Olympic champion swimmer Penny Heyns arrived
at the pool to begin her training. Yet, day after day, the only
thing that kept rising to the surface was her discontent. So,
reuniting with her longtime coach, Heyns somehow found a way to
summon the energy and motivation to take on the challenge one more
time. She has no regrets. By Michael Arkush.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DINING (Moved in ``d'' category) &LR;  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LONG-ISLAND-WINE (Peconic, N.Y.) _ Wine Talk Column: The Long
Island wine business is booming; it's almost giddy from its own
success. Handsome new wineries are opening, old ones are changing
hands for astonishing prices, new vineyards are springing up, and
suddenly, there isn't enough wine to go around. By Frank J. Prial.
</P>
<P>
   PARMIGIANO (Undated) _ Most people who buy Parmigiano-Reggiano
never give a thought to the variations in the way it tastes. I
always assumed the flavor differences had to do with the aging
process or the quality of the cheese itself. Or so I thought until
last week, when I tasted Parmigiano-Reggiano produced in fall,
winter, spring and summer. I was amazed at how distinctive each one
was. By Marian Burros.
</P>
