<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Thursday, July 27, 2000 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ It struck me, in fact, that Harry Potter bears
a greater resemblance to Anne of Green Gables. Both children are
orphans. Both have an undeniable personal magnetism. Both, enduring
cruelty and emotional neglect during childhood, enter a whole new
world at age 11 _ Anne to the enchanting Prince Edwards Island,
Harry to the enchanted Hogwarts School for Witchcraft and Wizardry.
(McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ Both George W. Bush and his running mate, Dick
Cheney, are Yalies. Bush got gentleman Cs at Yale where he was
known to be something of a party animal. Bush, at least, went
straight through to get his degree. Cheney, who already is getting
roasted on late-night talk shows for his lack of excitement, could
make Bush's partying look like a society tea party. (Nethaway, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ Now that the feds have noticed that it's
dangerous to drive and talk on a cellular phone at the same time
(well, duh), why not give people who jabber while driving a
competitive outlet to show off that skill by holding a special Cell
Phone Olympics? (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
