</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Pack your hot-weather cosmetics into a bag that's new and pretty
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   They're a mixed bag _ everything from plastic and mesh to fabric
and vinyl. Some are just large enough to hold a lipstick, compact
and eyeliner. Others can accommodate your entire cache of cosmetic
goodies. But most makeup bags fit comfortably in a handbag or tote.
</P>
<P>
   If your bag suddenly looks tired, throw it out and start over
with a bright floral print, a sleek black number or a vivid-colored
tote. Some of these bags are elegant enough to double as evening
pouches.
</P>
<P>
   We rounded up five makeup bags and stocked them with a few
hot-weather essentials that won't put a dent in anyone's beauty
budget.
</P>
<P>
   Flower power
</P>
<P>
   Modella makeup bag ($5.59). From top, Maybelline Great Lash
Waterproof Mascara ($3.99), Wet 'N' Wild Lip pencil (99 cents),
``Playful'' fragrance from Bottled Emotion ($3.29), Sonia Kashuk
blusher brush ($8.99) and ``Bloom'' blusher ($7.99).
</P>
<P>
   Bag and most products from Big Kmart stores; blusher and brush
from Target stores.
</P>
<P>
   Weave a spell
</P>
<P>
   Silk-like basketweave makeup bag ($32). In the bag, Tree Tree
Solution Lip Balm ($4.75) and Clinique SunCare SPF 15 ($14.50).
From the left, Bliss Cuticle Smoother ($14), Hard Candy ``Pixie''
colored nail polish ($12), Chantecaille's Lip Gloss in Ambrosia
($20) and Trish McEvoy's retractable brush ($65).
</P>
<P>
   Bag and products from Neiman Marcus in Lenox Square.
</P>
<P>
   Basic black
</P>
<P>
   Faux leather bag ($16), gold mascara ($5), yellow eyeliner
pencil ($4.50), nail polish ($3.50), lipstick ($9), disposable nail
files ($1.75) and lipstick blotting papers ($4).
</P>
<P>
   Bag and products from Sephora in Lenox Square.
</P>
<P>
   Social butterfly
</P>
<P>
   Accessories Plus makeup bag ($8.50). From left, Evian water
atomizer ($3.99), Sungirl Oil-Free Sunscreen with glitter SPF 10
($5.99) and Prestige lip gloss ($2.50).
</P>
<P>
   Bag and products from Ulta stores.
</P>
<P>
   Pretty in pink
</P>
<P>
   Stuff Bag clear vinyl makeup tote ($8.99), Trim's scented salon
nail board (99 cents), Sonia Kashuk's ``Sadye Pink'' eye shadow
($5.99) and Bonne Bell's ``Go Berry Wild'' Lip Lix ($1.99).
</P>
<P>
   Bag and products from Target stores.
</P>
<P>
   Cool bag of tricks
</P>
<P>
   New York artist Maria Verel, who has made up the faces of first
lady Hillary Rodham Clinton, broadcast journalist Diane Sawyer and
designer Vera Wang, suggests five essentials for every woman's
makeup bag:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  A tinted moisturizer with a sunscreen. ``It gives you a lift
of color yet protects you from the sun.'' Her recommendation?
Clinique's City Block with an SPF15 or SPF25.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Revlon's ColorStay. ``For those who want a bit more color, try
this cream cheek color that's swim-proof and sweat-proof.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Wet 'N' Wild's lipliner No. 666. ``This color, which is like
your own lip color, looks fabulous on any woman. First apply Chap
Stick to your lips, then put on the lip liner.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Waterproof mascara. ``Lots of companies make one, including
Maybelline, Cover Girl and L'Oreal. And, if you have a steady hand,
you can use the mascara, on a fine brush, as a liner.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Cornsilk Pressed Powder. ``Apply this no color on your shiny
T-zone.''
</P>
