<P>
   KITCHEN-CONVERSATIONS _ Chicken on the grill has never been a
favorite of mine. It's hard to cook properly, often served under
done or dried to the bone. But a little beer has changed my mind.
Pop a top on a can of beer, drink half of it (or pour it out) and
lower the cavity of a whole fryer over it. Place the can/bird over
indirect heat on the grill for little more than an hour and you'll
get the best bird from the grill you've ever tasted. The skin will
be crisp _ the meat steamed from the inside from the beer.(Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GRILLED-CHICKEN _ Chicken on the grill has never been a favorite
of mine. It's hard to cook properly, often served under done or
dried to the bone. But a little beer has changed my mind. Pop a top
on a can of beer, drink half of it (or pour it out) and lower the
cavity of a whole fryer over it. Place the can/bird over indirect
heat on the grill for little more than an hour and you'll get the
best bird from the grill you've ever tasted. The skin will be crisp
_ the meat steamed from the inside from the beer. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
