<P>
   CONCORDE-CRASH _ GONESSE, France _ Working in a dull gray mist,
investigators and medical workers Wednesday began sifting through
the blackened wreckage of a chartered Air France Concorde that
crashed near Paris minutes after take-off Tuesday. As attention
turned to the supersonic aircraft's engines, the airline said that
its mechanics worked on one of the plane's engines just before
take-off. The airline would not say whether the work was done on
the No. 4 engine, the one that apparently caught fire and streamed
flames as the aircraft plunged to the ground. (Roughton, Cox News
Service). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS-0727 _ JERUSALEM _ While Palestinian leader
Yasser Afarat returned to a hero's welcome from the Camp David
summit, Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak returned to face even
worse political problems than he left two weeks ago. Palestinians
praised their leader for not giving into pressure during the 15-day
summit, but Barak's critics said that he'd offered too much and
they would resume attempts to bring down his government.
Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service). MOVED.
</P>
