NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, JULY 27 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday July 27. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-AIRFRANCE-CRASH-CONCORDE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, July 25) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, July 25,
about the history of the Concorde, misstated the last year in which
the Tupolev 144 flew. After the 1973 crash, the plane was used for
mail and cargo service starting in 1975, and briefly for passenger
service in 1977 and 1978.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-BUSH-BIO-IV-NYT (moved on Friday, JulY 21) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, July 21,
about Gov. George W. Bush's life in the five years after he left
Yale misstated the name of an agricultural company that hired him
in 1971. It was Strat &UR; us93 &LR; ford of Texas, not Stratford of Houston.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-NORTEL-INVEST (moved on Monday, July 24) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, July 24,
about talks on the potential sale of Nortel Networks' fiber optics
components business to Corning misspelled the name of a European
company that Wall Street has speculated might make a deal with
Corning. It is  &UR; cobi &LR; Pirelli &UR; coei &LR; , not Perelli.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-TAKAZAUCKAS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, July 25) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   An obituary of Albert Takazauckas sent by the New York Times
News Service on Tueday, July 25, misstated the day and place of his
death and the city where he lived. He died on Sunday at his home in
Oakland, Calif., not on Monday in Los Angeles. He did not live in
Manhattan.  &QL; 
