<P>
   (NYT24) PINEVILLE, Kent. -- July 26, 2000 --
ILLITERACY-UNEMPLOYMENT-2 -- Sounding the alarm, politicians and
advocates for the poor have begun putting entrenched illiteracy at
the root of privation in places like Appalachia and the Mississippi
Delta that economic growth has largely ignored. Marsha Hendrickson
reads with her daughter Crystal Turner, 7, and her son Jacob Debusk,
4, earlier this week. Hendrickson participated in a program to help
her prepare for finding a job. (Vincent Laforet/The New York Times)
</P>
