   &QL; 
 &UR; ONLINE _  &LR;  The Federal Trade Commission yesterday slapped
Macys.com, Toysrus.com and five other e-tailers with $1.5 million
in fines for guaranteeing shipments to consumers last holiday
season and then failing to deliver.
</P>
<P>
   The settlement covers tens of thousands of consumers and $39
million worth of purchases that were not shipped by the promised
date or failed to arrive at all, said Jodie Bernstein, director of
the FTC's Bureau of Consumer Protection, in a telephone interview
yesterday.  &UR; BY CAROL EMERT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; MORTGAGE _  &LR; In an effort to encourage low-income families to buy
homes, a major mortgage company and a community group have joined
forces to offer cheaper loans in 10 cities nationwide, including
Oakland.
</P>
<P>
   The program, announced yesterday, will offer $360 million in
loans over the next three years to people with limited resources
and poor credit histories.  &UR; BY VERNE KOPYTOFF &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; COMPUTING (Q&AMP;A COLUMN)_  &LR; Is there any way to print out my America
Online address book? I've tried everything I can think of.
</P>
<P>
   A: You can't print the AOL address book, and you can't export it
to another program that would let you print it. AOL's just peachy,
isn't it? But where there's a will, there's a way, and here it is:
You can print out a ``picture'' of the AOL address book just as it
appears on screen.  &UR; BY DAVID EINSTEIN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; PAYMENT _  &LR;  The phrase ``please send money'' is taking on a whole
new meaning thanks to Web sites that specialize in person-to-person
(P2P) payments.
</P>
<P>
   Chances are, sometime soon you'll get an e-mail requesting
money. And, no, it won't be a junk mail solicitation. It will be be
from your roommate requesting this month's rent; from a co-worker
asking for your share of yesterday's lunch date; from an eBay
seller requesting payment for an auction you won; or from your
college kid asking for book money.  &UR; BY BECKY WARING &LR;
</P>
